    Licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License
    (CC BY 4.0). You are free to share and adapt this material for any purpose,
    provided you give appropriate credit.

    Full license text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode
    SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-4.0

Suggested attribution:

    "Dave Rand — github.com/davidlrand/mame-system-media"


2. Third-party material preserved for emulation and research
------------------------------------------------------------

Some files are the intellectual property of Colonial Data Services Corp.
(Hamden, Connecticut) or of its customers, and are NOT mine to license. The
SB-80 product line was discontinued in the 1980s. These items include:

    - colonial-sb80/bootrom.bin
          Colonial Data Services boot ROM (1982).

    - the Colonial Data CP/M 2.2 (02.15) CBIOS contained in
      colonial-sb80/disks/sb80-1k.td0

    - the customer application and data files (TMS) contained in
      colonial-sb80/disks/sb80-1k.td0

They are included in good faith for historical preservation, research, and use
with the MAME emulator, on the basis that the original product is decades out of
production and otherwise unavailable. No copyright claim is made over them, and
their inclusion does not transfer any rights.

If you hold rights to any of this material and wish it removed, please open an
issue or contact me, and I will take it down promptly.

Underlying CP/M is the work of Digital Research, Inc.; no Digital Research
material is redistributed here beyond what was customarily present on a working
system disk of the period.
